<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4826] Subcolumn slice ends not respected</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4826</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When performing &lt;tt&gt;get_slice()&lt;/tt&gt; on a super column family with the &lt;tt&gt;supercolumn&lt;/tt&gt; argument set as well as a slice range (meaning you&apos;re trying to fetch a slice of subcolumn from a particular supercolumn), the slice ends don&apos;t seem to be respected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12612301">CASSANDRA-4826</key>
            <summary>Subcolumn slice ends not respected</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
